4En7abT2.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2055373840063299584/pl/5LYmZci1TI0eGa5h.m3u8?v=f92", "aspectRatio": [16, 9], "heightRatio": 56, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2055373840063299584/vid/avc1/480x270/sJsJGcFuXCJupWtm.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1332231334761119745/wMzlpuHi_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Acyn", "username": "Acyn"}, "content": "Massie: I\u2019m walking to an airplane to rejoin the most expensive congressional race in U.S. history. It\u2019s turned into a referendum on whether Israel gets to buy seats in Congress. And what they found out is that my seat is really expensive. By the time this is over, they will", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 476}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsUPFsEV", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 25, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8620703, "raw_content": "", "author": "kek_saved_the_world", "created": 1778888864862, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "CoyoteTan", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "media.scored.co", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsUPFsEV.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://media.scored.co/post/WT0zFZ0tuXly.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/GmaT6fRevx85r3zD.png", "width": 768, "content-type": "png", "height": 594}], "blurhash": "UWDl{4t7IUof00j[xuayM{ayofjs~qj[M{j[", "full_resolution": [1000, 1294]}, "title": "Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation sold 100% of their Microsoft \n$MSFT\n position\u2026\n", "last_comment_created": 1778893860601, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 2, "score_up": 25, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsUPG9kV", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 18, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8620877, "raw_content": "On the moonlit night of May 16, 1943, a squadron of young RAF pilots flew into the jaws of Nazi Germany on a mission so audacious it bordered on madness.Armed with a revolutionary \"bouncing bomb\" and led by the unflinching Wing Commander Guy Gibson, the men of 617 Squadron, soon to be immortalised as the Dam Busters, took to the skies in lumbering Lancasters, tasked with shattering the great dams of the Ruhr Valley and crippling the industrial engine of Hitler\u2019s war machine.What followed was a feat of precision flying, raw courage, and tragic sacrifice - etched forever into the history books of wartime legend.The 16/17th May marked this most famous raid of WW2, the destruction of the Ruhr dams with the bouncing bomb. The story is so well known and has been told so often I do not think I could do it any more justice than has already been written so many times.Instead, I propose to concentrate on the three leading characters of the story. They are 617 Squadron, RAF, its squadron leader, Wing Commander Guy Gibson, VC. and Barnes Wallis, the inventor of the bouncing bomb.617 squadron, better known as The Dambusters Squadron, came into being on 21st March, 1943 at Scampton in Lincolnshire, specifically at the direction of Air Marshall \u201cBomber\u201d Harris, Commanding Officer of Bomber Command. Harris personally appointed Gibson to command it and gave him carte blanche in selecting the personnel from any squadron in the RAF or attached Dominion air forces. At the time of his appointment and for some time afterwards Gibson was not allowed to be told the target, only that it was a very secret mission requiring very low altitude flying against a critical target.Read their remarkable story\nhttps://patriotrealm.com/4637-the-men-behind-the-legend-dam-busters", "author": "Patriotrealm", "created": 1778895298545, "profile_picture": "EIlq25Xck8e3", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "For the history buffs - The Dam Busters anniversary", "last_comment_created": 1778895298545, "content": "<p>On the moonlit night of May 16, 1943, a squadron of young RAF pilots flew into the jaws of Nazi Germany on a mission so audacious it bordered on madness.Armed with a revolutionary &quot;bouncing bomb&quot; and led by the unflinching Wing Commander Guy Gibson, the men of 617 Squadron, soon to be immortalised as the Dam Busters, took to the skies in lumbering Lancasters, tasked with shattering the great dams of the Ruhr Valley and crippling the industrial engine of Hitler\u2019s war machine.What followed was a feat of precision flying, raw courage, and tragic sacrifice - etched forever into the history books of wartime legend.The 16/17th May marked this most famous raid of WW2, the destruction of the Ruhr dams with the bouncing bomb. The story is so well known and has been told so often I do not think I could do it any more justice than has already been written so many times.Instead, I propose to concentrate on the three leading characters of the story. They are 617 Squadron, RAF, its squadron leader, Wing Commander Guy Gibson, VC. and Barnes Wallis, the inventor of the bouncing bomb.617 squadron, better known as The Dambusters Squadron, came into being on 21st March, 1943 at Scampton in Lincolnshire, specifically at the direction of Air Marshall \u201cBomber\u201d Harris, Commanding Officer of Bomber Command. Harris personally appointed Gibson to command it and gave him carte blanche in selecting the personnel from any squadron in the RAF or attached Dominion air forces. At the time of his appointment and for some time afterwards Gibson was not allowed to be told the target, only that it was a very secret mission requiring very low altitude flying against a critical target.Read their remarkable story\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://patriotrealm.com/4637-the-men-behind-the-legend-dam-busters\" target=\"_blank\">https://patriotrealm.com/4637-the-men-behind-the-legend-dam-busters</a></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 18, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsUPFbme", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 25, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "pocrime", "id": 8620694, "raw_content": "", "author": "TaxDollarsHardAtWork", "created": 1778888631293, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "SoulSnipper", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "notthebee.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsUPFbme.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://notthebee.com/article/courtroom-audio-female-judge-who-gave-boston-rifleman-a-lenient-sentence-for-shooting-at-cops-said-she-was-taking-a-risk-on-him", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Courtroom audio: Female judge wh